% Write `pdd/commands/checkup.py` implementing the `pdd checkup` CLI wrapper for `run_agentic_checkup`.

<include>context/python_preamble.prompt</include>

% Requirements
- Click command: `@click.command("checkup")`, `@click.pass_context`, `@track_cost`.
- Params:
  - `target` arg (positional, optional â€” required for issue mode)
  - `--no-fix` flag
  - `--timeout-adder` (float, default `0.0`)
  - `--no-github-state` flag
  - `--validate-arch-includes` flag (local mode â€” cross-validates `architecture.json` against module prompt `<include>` tags; mutually exclusive with `target` and `--pr`/`--issue`)
  - `--project-root` (path, used with `--validate-arch-includes`)
  - `--strict` flag (used with `--validate-arch-includes`)
  - `--pr <pr-url>` (PR-verification mode â€” verify an existing PR instead of opening one; requires `--issue`, mutually exclusive with `target`)
  - `--issue <issue-url>` (PR-mode companion to `--pr` â€” the source issue the PR is meant to resolve)
  - `--review-loop` (PR mode only â€” run the multi-reviewer ping-pong review/fix loop)
  - `--reviewers` (comma-separated reviewer roles, default `codex,claude`)
  - `--max-review-rounds` (int, default `5`)
  - `--max-review-cost` (float, default `10.0`)
  - `--max-review-minutes` (float, default `90.0`)
  - `--require-all-reviewers-clean/--no-require-all-reviewers-clean` (default true)
  - `--continue-on-reviewer-limit` (flag)
  - `--require-final-fresh-review/--no-require-final-fresh-review` (default true)
- Signature returns `Optional[Tuple[str, float, str]]`.
- Mode validation:
  - If `--validate-arch-includes` is set: `target`, `--pr`, `--issue` must all be `None`; dispatch to `run_validate_arch_includes_cli(...)` and return.
  - If `--review-loop` is set: require PR mode (`--pr` and `--issue`); reject `--no-fix`; validate max-review values are positive (`--max-review-rounds >= 1`, cost/minutes > 0).
  - If `--pr` or `--issue` is set: BOTH must be present; `target` must be `None`; validate `--pr` via `_parse_pr_url(pr_url)` (mention "GitHub pull-request URL" in error); validate `--issue` via `_is_github_issue_url(issue_url_opt)` (mention "GitHub issue URL" in error); use `issue_url_opt` as the effective issue URL.
  - Otherwise (default issue mode): require `target`; validate via `_is_github_issue_url(target)` (BadParameter with `param_hint="'TARGET'"` and message must mention "GitHub issue URL").
- Force `--no-fix` when `--pr` is set and `--review-loop` is NOT set (legacy PR verification still cannot push fixes). Print a warning to stderr explaining why and how to re-invoke if fixes were intended.
- `ctx.ensure_object(dict)`; read `quiet = ctx.obj.get("quiet", False)` and `verbose = ctx.obj.get("verbose", False)`.
- Call `run_agentic_checkup(issue_url=effective_issue_url, verbose=verbose, quiet=quiet, no_fix=no_fix, timeout_adder=timeout_adder, use_github_state=not no_github_state, pr_url=pr_url, review_loop=review_loop, reviewers=reviewers, max_review_rounds=max_review_rounds, max_review_cost=max_review_cost, max_review_minutes=max_review_minutes, require_all_reviewers_clean=require_all_reviewers_clean, continue_on_reviewer_limit=continue_on_reviewer_limit, require_final_fresh_review=require_final_fresh_review)` where `pr_url` is `None` in non-PR modes.
- If not quiet, `click.echo` exactly these lines:
  - `Status: Success|Failed`
  - `Message: {message}`
  - `Cost: ${cost:.4f}`
  - `Model: {model}`
- If `not success`: raise `click.exceptions.Exit(1)`; else return `(message, cost, model)`.
- Exception policy: re-raise `click.Abort` and `click.exceptions.Exit`; all other exceptions call `handle_error(exception, "checkup", ctx.obj.get("quiet", False))` and return `None`.

